264
00:23:04.634 --> 00:23:08.472
Apples. a nickel. Apples here.

265
00:23:08.638 --> 00:23:10.140
Yes. ma'am.

266
00:23:10.307 --> 00:23:13.185
Here you go. Thank you.
God bless you.

267
00:23:13.351 --> 00:23:15.479
Apples here.

268
00:23:15.729 --> 00:23:18.815
Big. delicious apples here.

269
00:23:49.554 --> 00:23:52.015
All right! All right!

270
00:23:53.850 --> 00:23:54.893
Yeah?

271
00:23:55.644 --> 00:23:57.854
Miss Hannigan. I'm Grace Farrell.

272
00:23:58.021 --> 00:24:00.107
The New York Board of Orphans
sent me.

273
00:24:02.275 --> 00:24:05.362
My goodness. won't you come in?

274
00:24:05.570 --> 00:24:07.864
- Thank you.
- Right this way.

275
00:24:08.657 --> 00:24:10.575
Well. welcome.

276
00:24:10.742 --> 00:24:13.245
- Welcome to our happy home.
- Off my foot. Molly!

277
00:24:13.411 --> 00:24:14.454
- Thank you.
- Ladies.

278
00:24:14.621 --> 00:24:16.039
Smell that perfume.

279
00:24:16.206 --> 00:24:18.041
- And your name was?
- Grace Farrell.

280
00:24:18.208 --> 00:24:20.961
- She wants a girl to clean her house.
- Aptly named.

281
00:24:21.128 --> 00:24:24.756
- I bet it's gonna be me!
- I'm here to inquire about an orphan.

282
00:24:25.340 --> 00:24:28.927
Grace. I can explain the whole thing.
What happened was...

283
00:24:29.136 --> 00:24:33.974
...the child bribed Mr. Bundles
to smuggle her out of here.

284
00:24:34.224 --> 00:24:37.519
I should've called Mr. Donatelli.
but the truth is...

285
00:24:37.727 --> 00:24:40.313
...I just saw red.
so I called the cops instead.

286
00:24:40.480 --> 00:24:44.359
Anyway she's back. everything's fine.
All's well that ends well.

287
00:24:44.609 --> 00:24:47.529
No harm. no foul.
my little scissors legs?

288
00:24:47.988 --> 00:24:50.866
What are you talking about?

289
00:24:53.285 --> 00:24:58.415
Are you peddling beauty products?
I don't need beauty products.

290
00:24:59.082 --> 00:25:03.962
If that's what you're doing.
peddle yourself right out of here.

291
00:25:04.171 --> 00:25:08.550
I am the private secretary
to Oliver Warbucks.

292
00:25:08.758 --> 00:25:10.927
The Oliver Warbucks?

293
00:25:12.387 --> 00:25:16.933
- Oliver Warbucks the millionaire?
- No. the billionaire.

294
00:25:18.310 --> 00:25:19.936
Holy Mary. Mother of God.

295
00:25:20.145 --> 00:25:24.816
Mr. Warbucks would like to invite
an orphan to spend a week with him.

296
00:25:25.609 --> 00:25:26.943
I'm here to select one.

297
00:25:27.194 --> 00:25:29.321
That's just wonderful.

298
00:25:29.571 --> 00:25:31.907
What kind of orphan did he
have in mind?

299
00:25:32.115 --> 00:25:33.950
Well...

300
00:25:34.117 --> 00:25:35.660
...friendly.

301
00:25:36.411 --> 00:25:37.454
Intelligent.

302
00:25:37.829 --> 00:25:41.958
M-I-S-S-I-S-S-I-P-P-I.

303
00:25:42.792 --> 00:25:44.002
And I'1aPPY-

304
00:25:58.808 --> 00:26:02.854
- How old?
- Well. age doesn't really matter.

305
00:26:05.732 --> 00:26:07.150
Seven.

306
00:26:08.318 --> 00:26:11.655
Eight. Nine.

307
00:26:12.239 --> 00:26:13.281
Ten?

308
00:26:13.490 --> 00:26:15.408
Yes. 10 is just fine.

309
00:26:15.659 --> 00:26:17.202
Ten?

310
00:26:17.369 --> 00:26:19.663
I'm sorry. I almost forgot.

311
00:26:19.829 --> 00:26:24.584
- Mr. Warbucks prefers red hair.
- A 10-year-old redhead?

312
00:26:24.834 --> 00:26:27.254
Nope. Sorry. ain't got it.

313
00:26:27.462 --> 00:26:29.798
What about this child?

314
00:26:30.048 --> 00:26:32.384
- Annie?
- Yes.

315
00:26:34.844 --> 00:26:36.805
You don't want Annie.

316
00:26:37.055 --> 00:26:38.807
Why not?

317
00:26:39.975 --> 00:26:41.643
She's...

318
00:26:41.935 --> 00:26:43.270
She's a drunk.

319
00:26:44.938 --> 00:26:46.815
Fiddle-faddle.

320
00:26:47.065 --> 00:26:50.568
How'd you like to spend a week
with Mr. Warbucks at his house?

321
00:26:51.152 --> 00:26:55.240
Oh. boy! I would love to.
I would really. really love to.

322
00:26:55.490 --> 00:26:58.118
Wait! Slow down!
Hold on there!

323
00:26:58.868 --> 00:27:02.205
You can have any orphan in the whole
orphanage except Annie.

324
00:27:02.372 --> 00:27:03.415
Why?

325
00:27:03.623 --> 00:27:08.128
She's got it coming to her.
and I don't mean a week of luxury.

326
00:27:08.378 --> 00:27:11.381
- She's got to learn to know her place.
- Her place?

327
00:27:11.631 --> 00:27:13.258
Annie is entirely too cheeky.

328
00:27:13.842 --> 00:27:17.512
- Mr. Warbucks likes cheeky orphans.
- Tough!

329
00:27:18.263 --> 00:27:22.726
I assume your resistance has to do with
Mr. Donatelli and the Board of Orphans.

330
00:27:22.976 --> 00:27:24.978
Don't assume nothing. sweetheart.

331
00:27:25.186 --> 00:27:27.063
Mr. Warbucks knows Mr. Donatelli.

332
00:27:27.314 --> 00:27:29.190
- Is that a fact?
- Yes. it is.

333
00:27:29.399 --> 00:27:34.362
It's also a fact that he said how many
people he had lined up for your job.

334
00:27:36.906 --> 00:27:38.408
- Is that a fact?
- Yes.

335
00:27:38.950 --> 00:27:42.287
It's awful to be out of work.
isn't it. Miss Hannigan?

336
00:27:45.248 --> 00:27:46.708
Just terrible.

337
00:27:47.083 --> 00:27:48.501
Leaping lizards!

338
00:27:48.752 --> 00:27:52.839
-"Leaping lizards."
- The limousine is waiting.

339
00:27:56.801 --> 00:27:58.011
- My dog.
- What?

340
00:27:58.803 --> 00:28:01.014
Here. Sandy. Come here.

341
00:28:01.306 --> 00:28:03.725
He's really nice. Really good.

342
00:28:03.933 --> 00:28:06.644
He never jumps up on people.

343
00:28:08.563 --> 00:28:13.526
He's a very sweet dog. but really.
I don't think Mr. Warbucks--

344
00:28:13.735 --> 00:28:16.237
- Then I'm not coming.
- What?

345
00:28:16.488 --> 00:28:19.157
She's going to send him to
the sausage factory.

346
00:28:19.449 --> 00:28:22.786
- She said so herself.
- I'm not zoned for dogs.

347
00:28:22.994 --> 00:28:26.873
- We'll take the dog.
- Oh. boy!

348
00:28:32.670 --> 00:28:34.214
Bye. Annie!

349
00:28:35.799 --> 00:28:39.177
I'll be back.
I'll bring everybody presents.

350
00:28:46.643 --> 00:28:51.189
Bye. Molly. See you soon.
Bye. Pepper. Bye. Duffy.

351
00:29:31.229 --> 00:29:34.858
Is this a train station?
Are we going on a train?

352
00:29:35.066 --> 00:29:37.819
No. this is Mr. Warbucks' house.

353
00:29:44.242 --> 00:29:45.994
Leaping lizards.

354
00:30:00.675 --> 00:30:05.180
This is Punjab. He and the Asp
are Mr. Warbucks' bodyguards.

355
00:30:07.223 --> 00:30:09.851
Come along. Let's get you settled.

356
00:31:17.085 --> 00:31:18.753
Been to the zoo. Miss Farrell?

357
00:31:18.962 --> 00:31:20.213
Not recently. Drake.

358
00:31:20.380 --> 00:31:22.340
- Has the organ been tuned?
- Yes. miss.

359
00:31:22.507 --> 00:31:23.550
- Pool heated?
- Yes.

360
00:31:23.716 --> 00:31:25.093
- Tennis net up?
- Yes.

361
00:31:25.260 --> 00:31:26.636
- French doors fixed?
- Yes.

362
00:31:26.803 --> 00:31:28.304
- Elevator oiled?
- Yes.

363
00:31:28.471 --> 00:31:29.847
- Typewriter repaired?
- Yes.

364
00:31:30.098 --> 00:31:31.766
- Second Teletype installed?
- Yes.

365
00:31:32.016 --> 00:31:35.812
- Are you allergic to dogs. Drake?
- No. filth.

366
00:31:36.062 --> 00:31:38.481
- Is dinner under way. Mrs. Pugh?
- Yes. miss.

367
00:31:38.648 --> 00:31:41.859
Preparing his favorite.
Texas grapefruit. Virginia ham...

368
00:31:42.026 --> 00:31:47.073
...Idaho potatoes. Wisconsin cheese.
Washington apples and baked Alaska.

369
00:31:47.407 --> 00:31:50.159
I have an announcement to make.

370
00:31:50.410 --> 00:31:54.372
This is Annie. and she'll
be staying with us for a week.

371
00:31:54.956 --> 00:31:56.791
This is her dog. Sandy.

372
00:31:57.000 --> 00:31:59.335
He'll be staying with me.

373
00:31:59.502 --> 00:32:01.504
May I take your sweater. miss?

374
00:32:01.713 --> 00:32:05.008
- Will I get it back?
- Of course. miss!

375
00:32:06.551 --> 00:32:09.554
What would you like to do first?

376
00:32:14.892 --> 00:32:19.814
The windows. then the floors.
that way if I drip--

377
00:32:21.399 --> 00:32:25.945
You don't understand. You don't
have to do any cleaning here.

378
00:32:26.112 --> 00:32:27.488
I won't?

379
00:32:27.655 --> 00:32:29.407
How am I gonna earn my keep?

380
00:32:29.574 --> 00:32:31.868
You're our guest. Annie.

381
00:32:32.535 --> 00:32:35.496
Cecilie will pick out all your clothes

382
00:32:35.663 --> 00:32:38.499
Blue is her best color.
No. red. I think.

383
00:32:38.666 --> 00:32:41.669
Your bath is drawn by Mrs. Greer

384
00:32:41.836 --> 00:32:44.672
Soap. No. bubbles. I think.

385
00:32:44.839 --> 00:32:47.717
Annette comes in to make your bed

386
00:32:47.884 --> 00:32:50.720
The silk? No. the satin sheets. I think.

387
00:32:50.887 --> 00:32:54.432
I think I'm gonna like it here

388
00:33:31.260 --> 00:33:34.263
The swimming pool is down the stairs

389
00:33:34.430 --> 00:33:37.100
Inside the house? Oh. boy!

390
00:33:37.266 --> 00:33:40.353
The tennis court is in the rear

391
00:33:40.520 --> 00:33:43.481
- I never even picked up a racket.
- What?

392
00:33:43.648 --> 00:33:46.234
Have an instructor here at noon

393
00:33:46.401 --> 00:33:49.278
And get that Don Budge fellow.
if he's available.

394
00:33:49.445 --> 00:33:53.741
I think I'm gonna like it here

395
00:34:10.800 --> 00:34:13.845
When you wake. ring for Drake

396
00:34:14.011 --> 00:34:17.056
Drake will bring your tray

397
00:34:17.223 --> 00:34:24.105
When you're through
Mrs. Pugh comes to take it away

398
00:34:27.191 --> 00:34:31.571
- Annie!
- Come on. Annie! Come on!

399
00:34:33.114 --> 00:34:36.409
No need to pick up any toys

400
00:34:36.576 --> 00:34:39.287
That's okay. I haven't got any anyway.

401
00:34:39.454 --> 00:34:45.209
No finger will you lift. my dear

402
00:34:45.376 --> 00:34:48.421
We have but one request

403
00:34:48.588 --> 00:34:51.507
Please put us to the test

404
00:34:51.674 --> 00:34:58.055
I know I'm gonna like it here

405
00:35:09.192 --> 00:35:15.156
Used to room in a tomb
Where I'd sit and freeze

406
00:35:15.323 --> 00:35:18.326
Get me now. holy cow

407
00:35:18.493 --> 00:35:22.705
Could someone pinch me. please?

408
00:35:23.456 --> 00:35:26.000
Hold still. Hold still!

409
00:35:26.167 --> 00:35:28.169
You mutt!

410
00:36:07.083 --> 00:36:08.334
Hi. Annie!

411
00:36:08.543 --> 00:36:10.878
Got something for you.

412
00:36:20.680 --> 00:36:22.557
Here you are. Annie.

413
00:36:26.811 --> 00:36:29.605
We've never had a little girl

414
00:36:29.772 --> 00:36:32.900
We've never had a little girl
We've never had a little girl

415
00:36:33.067 --> 00:36:35.903
I'm very. very. very glad to volunteer

416
00:36:36.070 --> 00:36:39.240
I'm glad she's glad to volunteer

417
00:36:39.407 --> 00:36:42.159
We hope you understand

418
00:36:42.326 --> 00:36:45.329
Your wish is our command

419
00:36:45.496 --> 00:36:51.043
- I know I'm gonna like it here
- We know you're gonna like it here

420
00:36:59.051 --> 00:37:01.971
It's Mr. Warbucks. Don't worry now.

421
00:37:09.270 --> 00:37:11.731
- Welcome home. sir.
- Did the painting arrive?

422
00:37:11.939 --> 00:37:14.567
They're just uncrating it. sir.

423
00:37:26.120 --> 00:37:28.789
I don't like it. Send it back.
Any messages?

424
00:37:29.040 --> 00:37:32.835
President Roosevelt called three
times. He said it was urgent.

425
00:37:33.044 --> 00:37:35.504
Everything's urgent to a Democrat.
What else?

426
00:37:35.713 --> 00:37:39.592
Mr. Rockefeller. Mr. Vanderbilt.
Mr. DuPont. Mr. Carnegie.

427
00:37:39.842 --> 00:37:43.971
Wait! There's something interesting
in that woman's smile.

428
00:37:44.180 --> 00:37:48.142
I might learn to like her.
Hang her in my bathroom.

429
00:37:48.392 --> 00:37:52.188
No time for dinner tonight. Send out
for an American cheese sandwich.

430
00:37:52.396 --> 00:37:54.565
Come. let's get started.

431
00:37:58.027 --> 00:37:59.987
What the devil's going on here?

432
00:38:00.237 --> 00:38:04.116
This is the press representative.
Your image.

433
00:38:05.618 --> 00:38:07.244
Oh. yes.

434
00:38:08.746 --> 00:38:12.875
Pick him up. Punjab.
Get him another camera.

435
00:38:23.386 --> 00:38:26.847
Why do I smell wet dog'?

436
00:38:29.976 --> 00:38:32.478
Because we gave Sandy a bath.

437
00:38:32.728 --> 00:38:34.146
What's this?

438
00:38:34.355 --> 00:38:37.733
This is Annie. the orphan
who will be staying with us.

439
00:38:37.984 --> 00:38:39.485
What are you talking about?

440
00:38:40.695 --> 00:38:44.365
They wanted to take photos of you
sharing your home with an orphan.

441
00:38:44.532 --> 00:38:45.700
Only for a week.

442
00:38:45.950 --> 00:38:49.328
This doesn't look like a boy!
Orphans are boys.

443
00:38:49.578 --> 00:38:52.957
You didn't say a boy. You
just said an orphan. so I got a girl.

444
00:38:53.165 --> 00:38:54.417
I want a boy!

445
00:38:56.168 --> 00:38:59.005
I've got an interesting
smile too. sir.

446
00:38:59.255 --> 00:39:04.385
Couldn't you learn to like me. sir?
Hang me in the bathroom?

447
00:39:04.802 --> 00:39:08.681
- Take them back now.
- Sir. she just got here.

448
00:39:08.931 --> 00:39:11.892
That's okay. Miss Farrell.
We'll be okay.

449
00:39:12.393 --> 00:39:17.189
It was nice meeting you anyhow.
I sure do like your place.

450
00:39:17.440 --> 00:39:21.527
- Thank you. Annette.
- Annie. I've had a swell time.

451
00:39:21.777 --> 00:39:25.448
The Asp drove us here in
a car the size of a train.

452
00:39:25.698 --> 00:39:27.825
And Punjab put a spell on Sandy.

453
00:39:28.409 --> 00:39:31.620
We made Drake sneeze.
And I played your pipe organ.

454
00:39:31.829 --> 00:39:34.832
Sandy got a bubble bath.

455
00:39:35.082 --> 00:39:38.085
I've had enough fun
to last me for years.

456
00:39:38.335 --> 00:39:41.630
It's a really swell idea
to have an orphan for a week.

457
00:39:42.339 --> 00:39:44.383
A really terrific idea.

458
00:39:44.550 --> 00:39:48.054
Even if it is only for your image.
even if I'm not the orphan...

459
00:39:48.220 --> 00:39:51.932
-...I'm glad you're doing it.
- I'm glad you approve.

460
00:39:52.141 --> 00:39:53.809
Let's get to work!

461
00:39:54.060 --> 00:39:57.188
Are you sure you need a boy?
Couldn't she stay?

462
00:39:57.438 --> 00:40:00.608
Whatever. but just for the week.

463
00:40:04.612 --> 00:40:06.781
- You know what?
- What?

464
00:40:07.031 --> 00:40:10.284
- I love you.
- I know.

465
00:40:10.534 --> 00:40:14.955
- Kiss me as only you can.
- You devil.

466
00:40:20.544 --> 00:40:22.588
Get away!

467
00:40:33.182 --> 00:40:38.187
Little girls. little girls
Everywhere I turn

468
00:40:38.354 --> 00:40:41.148
I can see them

469
00:40:42.608 --> 00:40:44.819
Little girls. little girls

470
00:40:44.985 --> 00:40:50.241
Night and day
I eat. sleep and breathe them

471
00:40:50.407 --> 00:40:53.828
I'm an ordinary woman

472
00:40:53.994 --> 00:40:56.789
With feelings

473
00:40:56.956 --> 00:41:01.043
I'd like a man to nibble on my ear

474
00:41:01.210 --> 00:41:06.215
But I'll admit. no man has bit

475
00:41:06.382 --> 00:41:11.178
So how come
I'm the mother of the year?

476
00:41:11.345 --> 00:41:14.640
How I hate little shoes. little socks

477
00:41:14.807 --> 00:41:19.520
And each little bloomer

478
00:41:20.771 --> 00:41:23.023
I'd have cracked years ago

479
00:41:23.190 --> 00:41:29.446
If it weren't for my sense of humor

480
00:41:30.322 --> 00:41:34.785
Some women are dripping
With diamonds

481
00:41:34.952 --> 00:41:39.748
Some women are dripping with pearls

482
00:41:39.915 --> 00:41:45.421
Lucky me. lucky me
Look at what I'm dripping with

483
00:41:45.588 --> 00:41:48.591
Little girls

484
00:42:10.905 --> 00:42:16.702
Little cheeks. little teeth
Everything around me is

485
00:42:16.869 --> 00:42:18.871
Little

486
00:42:20.206 --> 00:42:22.416
<i>If I wring little necks</i>

487
00:42:22.583 --> 00:42:29.465
Surely I would get an acquittal

488
00:42:29.632 --> 00:42:34.303
Someday I'll step on their freckles

489
00:42:34.470 --> 00:42:39.183
Some night I'll straighten their curls

490
00:42:39.350 --> 00:42:41.685
Send a flood. send the flu

491
00:42:41.852 --> 00:42:46.815
Anything that you can do
To little. little. little

492
00:42:48.651 --> 00:42:51.737
Little. little. little

493
00:42:53.822 --> 00:42:58.410
Little girls

494
00:43:05.501 --> 00:43:10.214
Someday I'll /and in the nuthouse

495
00:43:10.381 --> 00:43:14.510
With all the nuts and the squirrels

496
00:43:14.677 --> 00:43:20.099
There I'll stay. tucked away
Till the prohibition of

497
00:43:20.266 --> 00:43:24.687
Little

498
00:43:24.853 --> 00:43:28.774
Girls

499
00:43:39.952 --> 00:43:42.579
- Rooster!
- Sis.

500
00:43:43.831 --> 00:43:46.292
You're supposed to be in jail.

501
00:43:46.500 --> 00:43:49.128
- They let me out early.
- For good behavior.

502
00:43:49.336 --> 00:43:53.716
I want you to meet a friend of mine.
Lily St. Regis.

503
00:43:53.966 --> 00:43:57.928
- Named from the hotel.
- Room service.

504
00:43:58.178 --> 00:44:03.142
This afternoon. I put 10 on the nose
of a beautiful horse at 8-1.

505
00:44:03.392 --> 00:44:06.478
Sure enough. the scum-bum
took off and whipped the pack.

506
00:44:06.645 --> 00:44:07.855
No kidding?

507
00:44:08.105 --> 00:44:13.485
The thing is. I got delayed
and I didn't have time to cash in.

508
00:44:13.652 --> 00:44:18.907
Eighty bucks. sis. first thing
in the morning. guaranteed.

509
00:44:19.158 --> 00:44:23.329
All I need is 5 to tide me over.

510
00:44:23.954 --> 00:44:26.790
Not even a nickel for the subway.

511
00:44:26.999 --> 00:44:29.501
Come on. sis.

512
00:44:31.628 --> 00:44:36.759
I bet Miss Sticky-Fingers here
can loan you a lousy 5 bucks.

513
00:44:37.259 --> 00:44:39.303
I beg your pardon. I'm sure.

514
00:44:39.553 --> 00:44:43.932
But I don't stoop to what you're
incinerating.

515
00:44:44.767 --> 00:44:47.227
Give me back my goods. toots.

516
00:45:04.745 --> 00:45:06.455
Okay. Rooster.

517
00:45:06.663 --> 00:45:11.210
If I loan you 5 bucks. will you
take this dumb hotel out of here?

518
00:45:11.418 --> 00:45:13.462
I'm sorry. sis. Lily.

519
00:45:14.421 --> 00:45:17.299
Not even a nickel for the subway.

520
00:45:17.758 --> 00:45:20.177
You and her have the same mother?

521
00:45:38.821 --> 00:45:40.864
Rooster!

522
00:45:50.916 --> 00:45:55.254
Betcha he reads
Betcha she sews

523
00:45:55.421 --> 00:45:59.299
Maybe she's made me
A closet of clothes

524
00:45:59.466 --> 00:46:04.054
Maybe they're strict
As straight as a line

525
00:46:04.221 --> 00:46:10.102
Don't really care
As long as they're mine

526
00:46:11.520 --> 00:46:16.483
So maybe now this prayer's

527
00:46:16.650 --> 00:46:21.447
The last one of its kind

528
00:46:21.613 --> 00:46:26.910
Won't you please come get your baby?

529
00:46:27.077 --> 00:46:31.248
Maybe

530
00:46:42.718 --> 00:46:45.762
This room's bigger than Grant's tomb.

531
00:46:47.097 --> 00:46:48.682
Me too.

532
00:46:50.601 --> 00:46:53.061
Come on. Sandy. Come on!

533
00:46:57.357 --> 00:46:58.525
In conclusion...

534
00:46:58.734 --> 00:47:03.697
...because your country has raised its
voice loud and clear for democracy...

535
00:47:03.947 --> 00:47:07.034
...I will extend to you a credit line...

536
00:47:07.242 --> 00:47:09.828
...for 35 of my new fighter-bombers.

537
00:47:10.329 --> 00:47:15.000
That will come with a year's supply
of spare parts and ammunition--

538
00:47:15.250 --> 00:47:16.460
What's this?

539
00:47:16.668 --> 00:47:20.547
Sandy's not used to sleeping
by himself. He gets lonesome.

540
00:47:22.341 --> 00:47:23.425
Where were we?

541
00:47:24.426 --> 00:47:27.012
-"Ammunition." sir.
- Are you getting a lot done?

542
00:47:27.221 --> 00:47:30.641
I'd get a lot more done
if certain people...

543
00:47:31.808 --> 00:47:35.979
If Franklin Delano Roosevelt
would leave me alone.

544
00:47:36.230 --> 00:47:37.856
Six calls since I got home.

545
00:47:38.065 --> 00:47:41.652
- What's he want?
- My support for the New Deal.

546
00:47:41.902 --> 00:47:44.696
He is our president. sir.

547
00:47:45.113 --> 00:47:46.615
Punjab!

548
00:47:47.074 --> 00:47:51.578
Remove this animal and its young
mistress along with it.

549
00:47:52.120 --> 00:47:57.125
Dear Richie. this letter will serve
as confirmation of correspondence...

550
00:47:57.334 --> 00:48:02.172
...concerning the details
of your extended deferment.

551
00:48:03.799 --> 00:48:05.300
--On or before September 1.

552
00:48:05.551 --> 00:48:10.597
If you cannot meet that deadline.
you will be charged interest.

553
00:48:10.847 --> 00:48:13.976
Six percent. Cordially. et cetera.

554
00:48:16.979 --> 00:48:22.109
P.S. One of my companies
is developing bomb-proof glass.

555
00:48:22.484 --> 00:48:28.365
This may be of interest to you
if the global situation deteriorates.

556
00:48:31.660 --> 00:48:34.955
- What was that?
- Well done. Sandy.

557
00:48:35.163 --> 00:48:38.375
- Was that man trying to kill you?
- That will be all.

558
00:48:38.625 --> 00:48:40.836
Yes. sir. Come along. dear.

559
00:48:42.004 --> 00:48:44.798
- Who'd want to kill Mr. Warbucks?
- The Bolsheviks.

560
00:48:45.048 --> 00:48:47.509
He's proof that
the American system works...

561
00:48:47.718 --> 00:48:50.178
...and Bolsheviks don't
want anyone to know.

562
00:48:50.679 --> 00:48:53.849
The Bolsheviks? Leaping lizards!

563
00:49:04.526 --> 00:49:07.821
Get your dog out of my pool!

564
00:49:07.988 --> 00:49:11.450
He thought you were drowning.
He was trying to save your life.

565
00:49:11.617 --> 00:49:16.038
- Go on. you mutt. Get out of here.
- Come on.

566
00:49:26.715 --> 00:49:28.508
Like my suit?

567
00:49:28.842 --> 00:49:30.260
What? Oh. yes.

568
00:49:30.469 --> 00:49:32.095
Miss Farrell picked it out.

569
00:49:32.304 --> 00:49:37.017
- Never thought I'd get used to a girl.
- Girls are easier to get used to.

570
00:49:37.267 --> 00:49:41.396
Like Miss Farrell.
she does all the work around here.

571
00:49:41.647 --> 00:49:45.025
- You don't know her first name.
- I do. It's Grace.

572
00:49:45.233 --> 00:49:48.987
She thinks you're the greatest thing
since sliced bread.

573
00:49:49.196 --> 00:49:50.238
I beg your pardon.

574
00:49:50.447 --> 00:49:54.826
I know it's none of my business.
but you never notice anything.

575
00:49:58.789 --> 00:50:00.874
Sliced bread.

576
00:50:01.583 --> 00:50:06.713
Wilhelm. please offer your son my
congratulations on his engagement.

577
00:50:07.172 --> 00:50:11.134
Hold on. Buy copper.

578
00:50:11.385 --> 00:50:16.515
Tell the crown prince
that my yacht in Monte Carlo...

579
00:50:16.765 --> 00:50:21.728
...is entirely at his disposal.

580
00:50:21.937 --> 00:50:25.482
Hold on. More copper.

581
00:50:25.691 --> 00:50:29.486
- Don't encourage her. Punjab.
- Maybe I should take her out.

582
00:50:29.736 --> 00:50:34.950
- Where do you want to go?
- To meet President Roosevelt.

583
00:50:36.910 --> 00:50:42.040
- How about a movie?
- Pepper went to a movie once.

584
00:50:42.332 --> 00:50:46.503
She said it was swell.
and Miss Hannigan goes all the time.

585
00:50:46.753 --> 00:50:50.924
- Take her to the Radio City Music Hall.
- Aren't you going to take me?

586
00:50:51.174 --> 00:50:55.011
Me? Annie. you may think
that Miss Farrell does all the work...

587
00:50:55.262 --> 00:50:59.057
...but I'm a very busy man.

588
00:50:59.307 --> 00:51:02.185
I know. Didn't mean
to get in the way. Mr. Warbucks.

589
00:51:02.394 --> 00:51:06.356
Nobody has to take me.
I'll go practice my backhand.

590
00:51:10.902 --> 00:51:15.949
Pepper lies a lot. She probably
hasn't been to a movie either.

591
00:51:16.616 --> 00:51:20.746
Actually. I think it's better when
you don't know what you're missing.

592
00:51:23.707 --> 00:51:29.629
Punjab. buy out the 8:00 show.
Let's all go to the movies.

593
00:51:34.176 --> 00:51:39.765
- You should leave your hair down.
- No. I couldn't.

594
00:51:39.931 --> 00:51:42.601
Miss Hannigan says
a man don't look at your brains.

595
00:51:42.768 --> 00:51:44.644
Oh. really? My goodness.

596
00:51:44.811 --> 00:51:47.689
Come on. let's go to the movies.

597
00:51:47.939 --> 00:51:50.400
Let's go see the stars.

598
00:51:51.234 --> 00:51:53.445
Cowboy heroes

599
00:51:53.612 --> 00:51:55.405
Cops and robbers

600
00:51:55.572 --> 00:51:57.491
Glamour and strife

601
00:51:57.657 --> 00:52:00.118
Bigger than life

602
00:52:03.914 --> 00:52:08.043
Sitting in the darkness

603
00:52:08.210 --> 00:52:12.380
What a world to see

604
00:52:12.547 --> 00:52:16.551
Let's go to the movies. Annie

605
00:52:16.718 --> 00:52:21.598
Wait and see

606
00:52:23.058 --> 00:52:24.893
Bette Davis is probably lying

607
00:52:25.060 --> 00:52:27.145
And Greta Garbo is probably crying

608
00:52:27.312 --> 00:52:31.733
While Robert Taylor
Is locked in her dying embrace

609
00:52:31.900 --> 00:52:36.071
Chico and Groucho and Chaplin
And Lloyd are all super

610
00:52:36.238 --> 00:52:37.906
Sweet Mickey Mouse
Shirley Temple

611
00:52:38.073 --> 00:52:39.574
And dear Jackie Cooper

612
00:52:39.741 --> 00:52:43.328
Let's go to the movies

613
00:52:43.495 --> 00:52:47.916
Let's go see the stars

614
00:52:52.087 --> 00:52:54.297
Fred and Ginger

615
00:52:54.464 --> 00:52:56.842
Spinning madly

616
00:53:13.567 --> 00:53:18.488
Anything you can imagine

617
00:53:20.407 --> 00:53:22.576
Songs and romance

618
00:53:22.742 --> 00:53:25.161
Life is a dance

619
00:53:27.664 --> 00:53:32.002
Sitting in the darkness

620
00:53:32.168 --> 00:53:36.590
Popcorn on your knee

621
00:53:36.756 --> 00:53:40.886
Give the maid the night off

622
00:53:42.178 --> 00:53:45.223
Turn the kitchen light off.

623
00:53:45.640 --> 00:53:50.186
Let's go to the movies. Annie

624
00:53:50.353 --> 00:53:55.025
You and me

625
00:54:22.886 --> 00:54:26.348
Welcome to the movies

626
00:54:26.514 --> 00:54:30.143
Welcome to the stars

627
00:54:30.310 --> 00:54:33.855
Welcome to this
Grand illusion

628
00:54:34.022 --> 00:54:35.732
All of it's yours

629
00:54:35.899 --> 00:54:37.901
Right through these doors

630
00:54:39.778 --> 00:54:43.281
Every plot's a dilly

631
00:54:43.448 --> 00:54:46.785
This we guarantee

632
00:54:47.160 --> 00:54:50.789
Welcome to the movies

633
00:54:51.122 --> 00:54:54.084
Wait and see

634
00:55:12.352 --> 00:55:14.688
Let's go to the movies

635
00:55:16.564 --> 00:55:20.735
Let's go see the stars

636
00:55:20.902 --> 00:55:23.321
Headlines holler

637
00:55:23.488 --> 00:55:25.156
Big depression

638
00:55:25.323 --> 00:55:27.367
What do we care?

639
00:55:27.534 --> 00:55:29.911
Movies are there

640
00:55:30.286 --> 00:55:34.457
Only happy endings
Boy get's girl

641
00:55:34.624 --> 00:55:38.545
That's our recipe

642
00:55:38.712 --> 00:55:41.965
Welcome to our lovely

643
00:55:42.132 --> 00:55:45.844
M-O- V-I-E

644
00:56:18.585 --> 00:56:21.796
We love to go to RKO

645
00:56:21.963 --> 00:56:25.258
Columbia. Universal

646
00:56:25.425 --> 00:56:28.678
Jack Warner and Sam Goldwyn and

647
00:56:28.845 --> 00:56:32.432
MGM and Zanuck
Here's to

648
