00:57:02.837 --> 00:57:04.756
So welcome

655
00:57:04.923 --> 00:57:08.676
To the movies

656
00:57:10.386 --> 00:57:12.847
Wait

657
00:57:13.014 --> 00:57:15.433
And

658
00:57:15.600 --> 00:57:17.519
See

659
00:57:36.162 --> 00:57:38.790
<i>For the "lady of the camellias</i>

660
00:57:41.251 --> 00:57:47.423
<i>- They're twice as large as usual.
- I'll have twice as many as usual</i>

661
00:57:47.715 --> 00:57:52.387
Twice as many?
I know what those things cost.

662
00:57:52.554 --> 00:57:55.682
And when she orders her hats
and dresses from you?

663
00:57:55.849 --> 00:57:57.225
They're an investment.

664
00:57:57.392 --> 00:58:02.188
You won't be young forever.
It's time you settled your future.

665
00:58:02.856 --> 00:58:05.733
I know the very man for you.

666
00:58:05.900 --> 00:58:08.361
- Really?
- Yes. really.

667
00:58:11.364 --> 00:58:16.161
- No one has ever loved you as I do.
- True. but what can I do about it?

668
00:58:18.121 --> 00:58:21.416
You should go away
and not see me anymore.

669
00:58:24.627 --> 00:58:30.091
Don't go in anger. Laugh at yourself
a little. as I laugh at myself.

670
00:58:30.258 --> 00:58:34.137
Come and talk to me once in a while
in a friendly way.

671
00:58:35.471 --> 00:58:37.390
That's too much and not enough.

672
00:58:37.557 --> 00:58:40.226
Believe in love. Marguerite.

673
00:58:40.476 --> 00:58:41.978
So you do love him.

674
00:58:44.439 --> 00:58:48.318
Dare to tell me that you love him.
and you're free of me forever.

675
00:58:50.486 --> 00:58:52.071
I love him.

676
00:58:57.535 --> 00:59:01.915
Come in here. all of you.
See this woman? You know her.

677
00:59:02.165 --> 00:59:04.459
Listen to what I'm going to say.

678
00:59:04.626 --> 00:59:07.086
I accepted her favors.
I thought she loved me.

679
00:59:07.337 --> 00:59:10.256
Let her make sacrifices
when others had more to give.

680
00:59:10.423 --> 00:59:13.718
But bear witness. I owe her nothing.

681
00:59:13.927 --> 00:59:15.553
Take it. Go on. take it.

682
00:59:15.803 --> 00:59:19.891
<i>Buy camellias. Buy diamonds
Buy carriages. Buy a grave.</i>

683
00:59:20.725 --> 00:59:26.272
You know how to treat a woman as she
deserves. Like the cheat this one is.

684
00:59:33.112 --> 00:59:34.822
Marguerite.

685
00:59:41.162 --> 00:59:42.914
Oh. it's you.

686
00:59:45.041 --> 00:59:47.543
I've been down in the street
half the night...

687
00:59:47.710 --> 00:59:49.754
walking under your window...

688
00:59:49.921 --> 00:59:54.550
...wanting to come up.
but not daring to. I felt so guilty.

689
00:59:55.343 --> 00:59:58.012
Don't think such things. Marguerite.

690
00:59:58.179 --> 01:00:00.515
Even if we can't
go to the country today...

691
01:00:00.765 --> 01:00:05.478
...think of how happy we were once
and how happy we'll be again.

692
01:00:05.728 --> 01:00:09.857
<i>Think of the day you found
the four-leaf clover.</i>

693
01:00:10.066 --> 01:00:15.113
Think of the vows that
we're going to make to each other.

694
01:00:15.989 --> 01:00:18.408
This is for life. Marguerite.

695
01:00:21.703 --> 01:00:22.996
Marguerite.

696
01:00:28.501 --> 01:00:30.086
Marguerite.

697
01:00:32.964 --> 01:00:36.968
No. don't leave me.
Marguerite. come back.

698
01:01:52.668 --> 01:01:55.004
Get her nightgown
behind the bathroom door.

699
01:01:55.171 --> 01:01:57.590
Certainly.

700
01:02:33.459 --> 01:02:36.504
- Miss Farrell.
- It's all right.

701
01:02:38.131 --> 01:02:40.174
- How did you learn that?
- Learn what?

702
01:02:40.425 --> 01:02:42.176
- That.
- What?

703
01:02:42.385 --> 01:02:45.179
- You put her to bed.
- You put her to bed too.

704
01:02:45.430 --> 01:02:47.265
- I did?
- Yes. you did.

705
01:02:47.515 --> 01:02:49.517
Good heavens.

706
01:03:12.081 --> 01:03:17.920
- That was a wonderful evening.
- I have to close a factory.

707
01:03:18.087 --> 01:03:20.840
- About Annie.
- What about Annie?

708
01:03:21.299 --> 01:03:23.092
Could we keep her?

709
01:03:24.552 --> 01:03:29.348
You haven't seen that orphanage.
I can't bear to send her back there.

710
01:03:29.640 --> 01:03:32.101
Get a hold of yourself.
What's come over you?

711
01:03:32.351 --> 01:03:36.564
I'd take care of her.
You have plenty of room here.

712
01:03:36.814 --> 01:03:42.028
- We could take her on as your ward.
- Absolutely not.

713
01:03:42.195 --> 01:03:44.155
I love money. I love power.

714
01:03:44.405 --> 01:03:47.700
I do not now.
nor ever will. love children.

715
01:03:52.538 --> 01:03:56.667
Watching you with her last night.
I thought maybe...

716
01:03:58.169 --> 01:03:59.378
Yes?

717
01:04:07.637 --> 01:04:11.516
- I've just noticed something.
- Yes?

718
01:04:11.766 --> 01:04:15.228
You're awfully pretty
when you argue with me.

719
01:04:18.147 --> 01:04:20.441
- Thank you. sir.
- Oliver.

720
01:04:27.323 --> 01:04:32.328
Do you just love money and power
and capitalism?

721
01:04:33.663 --> 01:04:36.082
They'll never love you back.

722
01:04:36.332 --> 01:04:39.627
- Your teeth are crooked.
- I'll have them fixed.

723
01:04:39.877 --> 01:04:43.965
- I like them crooked.
- I'll leave them.

724
01:04:44.632 --> 01:04:46.092
Thank you.

725
01:04:48.553 --> 01:04:51.305
I could have the papers signed
this morning.

726
01:04:54.850 --> 01:05:01.315
- It means a great deal to you.
- Yes. it means a great deal to me.

727
01:05:01.482 --> 01:05:04.235
I'll do it myself.

728
01:05:08.197 --> 01:05:10.283
I could just kiss you!

729
01:05:14.036 --> 01:05:16.831
Grace. get her a little gift.

730
01:05:17.081 --> 01:05:18.624
That's a good idea.

731
01:05:18.916 --> 01:05:20.876
Something from Tiffany's. A locket.

732
01:05:22.795 --> 01:05:27.133
Be careful at that orphanage.
That woman's got claws and fangs.

733
01:05:42.690 --> 01:05:44.483
We got Annie.

734
01:05:49.155 --> 01:05:51.907
- We've got Annie?
- Yeah.

735
01:05:59.123 --> 01:06:01.751
She's like a shine on your shoes

736
01:06:01.917 --> 01:06:04.545
Or hearing a blues
That's great

737
01:06:10.092 --> 01:06:11.385
Makes you relax

738
01:06:11.552 --> 01:06:14.388
Like a big tax rebate

739
01:06:15.431 --> 01:06:17.058
We got Annie

740
