955
01:24:33.903 --> 01:24:36.197
Oh. boy!

956
01:24:58.470 --> 01:25:02.140
Marvelous!
Aren't Republicans ostentatious?

957
01:25:02.390 --> 01:25:07.061
Franklin. behave.
It's astonishing he's here at all.

958
01:25:11.107 --> 01:25:16.237
- What do you call this. Oliver?
- An autocopter.

959
01:25:16.571 --> 01:25:21.701
You don't need an airport.
They say it can land on a dime.

960
01:25:21.951 --> 01:25:26.748
- Whatever that may be.
- You being here means a great deal.

961
01:25:26.915 --> 01:25:33.338
It means nothing. It means only
that Annie wanted to meet you.

962
01:25:35.632 --> 01:25:40.762
- Nice to meet you. Mr. President.
- It's my pleasure. Annie.

963
01:25:41.137 --> 01:25:44.808
Thank you for bringing the old goat.
Make a New Dealer of him yet.

964
01:25:45.058 --> 01:25:48.269
- Inconceivable.
- Don't mind him. Oliver.

965
01:25:48.520 --> 01:25:50.104
Come along. Annie.

966
01:25:50.313 --> 01:25:55.443
My Uncle Theodore used to teach
his children to walk on stilts.

967
01:25:55.819 --> 01:25:59.656
I can't teach you that. I can teach you
to roll in a chair with wheels.

968
01:25:59.823 --> 01:26:01.491
My own private roller coaster.

969
01:26:02.325 --> 01:26:06.746
The New Deal is badly planned.
badly organized and administered.

970
01:26:06.996 --> 01:26:09.874
You don't think your
programs through.

971
01:26:10.124 --> 01:26:13.044
Think what you're going to do
to the economy!

972
01:26:13.253 --> 01:26:17.131
- People don't eat in the long run.
- People can't feed their children.

973
01:26:17.340 --> 01:26:19.551
The lucky ones are left in orphanages.

974
01:26:19.801 --> 01:26:22.178
The older ones steal. starve.

975
01:26:22.387 --> 01:26:25.056
This business
of this country is business--

976
01:26:25.306 --> 01:26:29.602
Take them off the dole and put
them to work. That's what I'll do.

977
01:26:29.811 --> 01:26:35.733
In the National Parks. clearing trails.
fighting fires. planting trees.

978
01:26:35.900 --> 01:26:38.862
- Hold it.
- I want to feed them and house them...

979
01:26:39.028 --> 01:26:40.071
...and pay them.

980
01:26:40.280 --> 01:26:42.365
Enough to send home
to their parents...

981
01:26:42.532 --> 01:26:46.619
...so they can hold their heads up
and be proud to be Americans.

982
01:26:46.786 --> 01:26:50.039
- That's a swell idea.
- It isn't a swell idea. Annie...

983
01:26:50.206 --> 01:26:52.000
...it's mistaken foolishness.

984
01:26:52.166 --> 01:26:54.377
Big-hearted and empty-headed.

985
01:26:54.586 --> 01:26:58.464
Which parks? Which children?
What will it cost?

986
01:26:58.715 --> 01:27:01.467
Who's going to organize it?
Who's going to run it?

987
01:27:02.677 --> 01:27:06.389
- I was hoping you would.
- Me?

988
01:27:06.598 --> 01:27:10.435
- And Annie.
- Leaping lizards!

989
01:27:10.935 --> 01:27:13.897
- Out of the question.
- How can I help?

990
01:27:14.147 --> 01:27:15.523
Wait a minute!

991
01:27:15.732 --> 01:27:18.693
- You can help recruit young people.
- Hold everything!

992
01:27:18.943 --> 01:27:23.156
They think their government
doesn't care whether they live or die.

993
01:27:23.406 --> 01:27:26.492
With your help.
we could convince them otherwise-

994
01:27:26.743 --> 01:27:28.286
I want to say something.

995
01:27:28.536 --> 01:27:33.082
There's a song I used to sing
in the orphanage when I was sad.

996
01:27:33.333 --> 01:27:36.878
- It always cheered me up.
- Eleanor!

997
01:27:37.670 --> 01:27:41.925
Just thinking about tomorrow

998
01:27:42.091 --> 01:27:47.138
Clears away the cobwebs
And the sorrow

999
01:27:47.305 --> 01:27:49.807
Till there's none

1000
01:27:49.974 --> 01:27:52.310
When I'm stuck with a day

1001
01:27:52.477 --> 01:27:56.189
That's gray and lonely

1002
01:27:56.356 --> 01:27:58.650
I just stick out my chin

1003
