- Be careful.

1143
01:41:36.049 --> 01:41:39.762
Oh. my goodness. Oh. my goodness.

1144
01:41:40.012 --> 01:41:42.055
Help me get UP-

1145
01:41:51.607 --> 01:41:53.901
Give me your hand.

1146
01:41:57.279 --> 01:42:00.824
It's a long way down.
Are you sure you want to do this?

1147
01:42:05.162 --> 01:42:07.498
- Wish me luck.
- Good luck.

1148
01:42:26.892 --> 01:42:32.523
We were starving. We needed the job
That's why we left our little girl.

1149
01:42:32.689 --> 01:42:39.446
- Wrapped in a newspaper.
- On the steps of the orphanage.

1150
01:42:47.579 --> 01:42:48.789
What's this?

1151
01:42:49.039 --> 01:42:52.334
This is Ralph and Shirley Mudge
from Hoboken. New Jersey.

1152
01:42:52.501 --> 01:42:53.794
Annie!

1153
01:42:58.048 --> 01:43:03.178
Ralph. look!
She still has the locket.

1154
01:43:17.901 --> 01:43:20.028
We finally found you.

1155
01:43:20.279 --> 01:43:22.823
You heard about the reward
on the radio.

1156
01:43:23.073 --> 01:43:25.534
- Reward?
- We don't have a radio.

1157
01:43:25.784 --> 01:43:27.411
- In the paper.
- Paper?

1158
01:43:27.661 --> 01:43:30.706
- What paper?
- How did you know Annie was here?

1159
01:43:30.956 --> 01:43:35.669
- The lady at the orphanage told us.
- I have her birth certificate here.

1160
01:43:37.337 --> 01:43:42.426
I've kept it close to my heart
all of these years.

1161
01:43:46.805 --> 01:43:48.765
"Ann Marie Mudge.

1162
01:43:49.016 --> 01:43:54.146
October 18. 1922."

1163
01:44:00.068 --> 01:44:01.987
I'll go pack.

1164
01:44:04.531 --> 01:44:07.618
Do you want me to help. baby?

1165
01:44:08.952 --> 01:44:10.621
No. thanks...

1166
01:44:11.371 --> 01:44:13.040
...Mom.

1167
01:44:42.861 --> 01:44:44.613
Come on.

1168
01:45:02.255 --> 01:45:04.549
A certified check!

1169
01:45:05.592 --> 01:45:09.972
We're so glad to have found Annie.
We don't need this.

1170
01:45:10.222 --> 01:45:16.103
- I'll take it back.
- Of course. we are poor people.

1171
01:45:17.145 --> 01:45:19.398
It would help us a lot.

1172
01:45:19.648 --> 01:45:24.611
We could buy her milk.
a warm blanket.

1173
01:45:26.363 --> 01:45:31.243
Put it in your pocket. Mrs. Mudge.

1174
01:45:36.123 --> 01:45:38.125
Come on. you guys.

1175
01:45:40.085 --> 01:45:45.215
- Oh. my goodness!
- We're never going to make it.

1176
01:45:45.465 --> 01:45:49.803
- We've found Fifth Avenue.
- Number one. Fifth Avenue.

1177
01:45:50.012 --> 01:45:53.348
We've got to go to 987.

1178
01:45:54.266 --> 01:45:58.145
- Molly. get on my back.
- Come on. you guys. help.

1179
01:46:02.274 --> 01:46:07.112
- Will the stores take this back?
- All your new clothes?

1180
01:46:08.030 --> 01:46:10.907
I guess so.
Don't you want to keep them?

1181
01:46:11.158 --> 01:46:16.288
My folks are poor. All these clothes
are going to make them feel bad.

1182
01:46:16.496 --> 01:46:22.377
- Take them to the orphanage.
- Certainly.

1183
01:46:22.753 --> 01:46:25.464
This will look so cute on Molly.

1184
01:46:28.008 --> 01:46:30.469
This will look good on Duffy.

1185
01:46:44.024 --> 01:46:48.278
Betcha my life
Is gonna be swell

1186
01:46:48.445 --> 01:46:49.905
Looking at them

1187
01:46:50.072 --> 01:46:54.076
It's easy to tell

1188
01:46:54.451 --> 01:46:58.371
And maybe I'll forget

1189
01:46:58.538 --> 01:47:02.292
How nice he was to me

1190
01:47:03.168 --> 01:47:09.549
And how I was almost his baby

1191
01:47:32.489 --> 01:47:34.491
It'll be fine

1192
01:47:34.658 --> 01:47:36.576
Nothing to fear

1193
01:47:36.743 --> 01:47:40.455
She'll be as happy
As she was here

1194
01:47:40.622 --> 01:47:44.126
Things have worked out
Much better than planned

1195
01:47:44.292 --> 01:47:46.128
It makes you smile

1196
01:47:46.294 --> 01:47:49.214
When fate takes a hand

1197
01:47:51.550 --> 01:47:54.386
<i>And I know I'll forget</i>

1198
01:47:54.553 --> 01:47:57.889
How much she meant to me

1199
01:47:58.056 --> 01:48:04.187
And how she was almost my baby

1200
01:48:05.230 --> 01:48:08.150
Maybe

1201
01:48:35.760 --> 01:48:37.512
- Did you get it?
- She has it.

1202
01:48:37.679 --> 01:48:39.347
Let me see it.

1203
01:48:40.140 --> 01:48:45.270
- I'd better keep it.
- Over my dead body.

1204
01:48:45.478 --> 01:48:48.398
That's the brightest thing I've
ever heard you say.

1205
01:48:48.565 --> 01:48:50.066
Ladies! Ladies!

1206
01:48:50.233 --> 01:48:54.112
- Help. Mr. Warbucks! Help!
- Get on the road!

1207
01:48:58.325 --> 01:49:01.077
We'll never find the house.

1208
01:49:01.244 --> 01:49:04.998
I wish I'd been outside New York City.

1209
01:49:07.250 --> 01:49:09.586
When I get my half!

1210
01:49:14.674 --> 01:49:16.927
- I say we go back.
- We can't.

1211
01:49:17.177 --> 01:49:19.221
We've been walking for 100 years!

1212
01:49:19.471 --> 01:49:23.475
- We're never going to get there.
- But we have to.

1213
01:49:23.725 --> 01:49:28.813
- Let's take a vote.
- All in favor of calling it quits?

1214
01:49:31.316 --> 01:49:35.654
- I'll get a gold lamÃ© number.
- In Atlantic City.

1215
01:49:35.904 --> 01:49:40.242
We aren't stopping
till we hit Atlantic City.

1216
01:49:43.662 --> 01:49:47.749
- Help. Mr. Warbucks!
- Shut up. kid.

1217
01:49:51.044 --> 01:49:54.005
Look. there's Sandy!

1218
01:49:57.133 --> 01:49:59.761
Come here! Come here!

1219
01:50:07.769 --> 01:50:10.689
Come on. let's go!

1220
01:50:11.898 --> 01:50:14.234
- Hurry up_
- Hurry! Hurry!

1221
01:50:17.195 --> 01:50:20.073
I can't run anymore.

1222
